    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make newspapers print retractions the same font, size and page as the original",
        "additional_details": "Here is an example of such a retraction...\r\n\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10156952942302272&set=a.10150366579832272&type=3&theater",
        "background": "Brexit has highlighted how the press (both sides) run stories that significantly impact and influence voters and often maintain dispute rather than promoting debate. Stories are later proven untrue and a tiny apology is printed at the back of the paper. This apology should match the original story.",
